                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1068">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00/1238a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="6" xml:id="d1068fn6">Repeated as telegrams Nos. 156 to
                        Nicaragua and 87 to Honduras.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-03T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 3, 1944—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>201. You are requested to discuss the subject matter of the Department’s
                    preceding telegram<note n="7" xml:id="d1068fn7">Telegram No. 200, <hi
                            rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> with your military, naval and legal
                    attachés, if available, and to request them very discreetly to note whether
                    there is any movement of arms or forces which indicate any intention of
                    interfering in any way in the Salvadoran revolutionary disturbance.</p>
                <pb facs="1103" n="1089" xml:id="pg_1089"/>
                <p>Please report to the Department any significant information pertaining to the
                        above.<note n="8" xml:id="d1068fn8">Replies from Guatemala, Nicaragua, and
                        Honduras (telegrams Nos. 217, 215, and 102 of April 4, respectively),
                        reported no indications of interference; telegrams not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
